SUMMARY:Nitty Gritty Dirt Band at American Music Theatre
DESCRIPTION:Nitty Gritty Dirt Band – All the Good Times: The Farewell Tour – 60 Years of Dirt\nNitty Gritty Dirt Band has been delighting audiences with their signature blend of country\, folk\, rock\, and roots music. Widely regarded as one of the most influential bands in American roots history\, their career spans multiple generations and includes timeless hits like “Mr. Bojangles\,” “Fishin’ in the Dark\,” “An American Dream\,” and “House at Pooh Corner.” \nThe All the Good Times Tour celebrates the band’s incredible legacy — from their groundbreaking Will the Circle Be Unbroken collaborations to their chart-topping radio favorites. With their trademark harmonies\, masterful musicianship\, and heartfelt storytelling\, The Nitty Gritty Dirt Band continues to prove that great music only gets better with age. \nJoining NGDB is emerging country artist Meels with her soulful voice\, heartfelt lyrics\, and modern country flair. Blending authentic storytelling with infectious melodies\, Meels is quickly capturing hearts and carving out her place in today’s country music scene. \nVIP1: The Nitty Gritty Front Row with Meet & Greet Experience   $305 \nIncludes: \n\nPremium reserved ticket in the front row\nInvitation to a private post-show meet & greet with the members of Nitty Gritty Dirt Band*\nExclusive signed 8×10 photo\nCommemorative VIP laminate\n\n*Not all members may be present \nVIP2: The Nitty Gritty Premium Seat with Meet & Greet Experience   $229 \nIncludes: \n\nPremium reserved ticket in first ten (10) rows\nInvitation to a private post-show meet & greet with the members of Nitty Gritty Dirt Band*\nExclusive signed 8×10 photo\nCommemorative VIP laminate\n\n*Not all members may be present \n\nCome Explore Our Lancaster Theaters and the Arts\n\n\nLive Theater\nLive Entertainment\nLive Music\n\n\n\nDinner Theaters\nMurder Mysteries\nThings To Do\n\n\n\nArtisan Collectives\nArt Galleries\nEvents Calendar
URL:https://lancasterpa.com/events-calendar/nitty-gritty-dirt-band-american-music-theatre/
