SUMMARY:Etiquette Dinner Theater at Log Cabin Restaurant
DESCRIPTION:Join us for an immersive dining experience where a multi-course meal is paired with live interactive theater. This elegant\, 1920s-set evening is a formal affair—guests are encouraged to dress in their finest. As guests dine\, actors humorously demonstrate proper (and improper) table manners through a playful story of competing etiquette experts and eager students. \nYour dinner will include a four-course meal\, starting with a soup and salad\, followed by either a beef\, chicken\, fish\, or vegetarian entree. The dessert will be Chef’s choice. When booking\, you will be asked to choose your preferred dish. \nThe dinner will begin promptly at 6:00 PM so we recommend arriving a few minutes prior to grab a drink and settle in.
